      "text": "This is fantastic feedback and a great set of next steps! You\u0027ve clearly grasped the potential here and are thinking about how to make it both more powerful and more demonstrative of the underlying concepts.\n\nLet\u0027s proceed by implementing a combination of features that offer high value and can be integrated smoothly into the existing structure. I think these make a great next batch:\n\n1.  **Symbolic QA Equation Viewer (4):** Easy to add and very helpful for understanding.\n2.  **Probabilistic Measurement (3):** Adds a key quantum-inspired concept with low complexity.\n3.  **Cycle Tracker (1):** Core to seeing the evolution; we\u0027ll start without animation.\n4.  **Export/Share (5):** Great utility feature for sharing states.\n\nLet\u0027s integrate these now.\n\n```html\n\u003c!DOCTYPE html\u003e\n\u003chtml lang\u003d\"en\"\u003e\n\u003chead\u003e\n    \u003cmeta charset\u003d\"UTF-8\"\u003e\n    \u003cmeta name\u003d\"viewport\" content\u003d\"width\u003ddevice-width, initial-scale\u003d1.0\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eQuantum Arithmetic Simulator v2\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cstyle\u003e\n        body {\n            font-family: sans-serif;\n            display: flex;\n            flex-wrap: wrap; /* Allow panels to wrap on smaller screens */\n            padding: 10px;\n            gap: 15px;\n            background-color: #f0f0f0;\n        }\n        .panel {\n            background-color: #fff;\n            padding: 15px;\n            border-radius: 8px;\n            box-shadow: 2px 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);\n            display: flex;\n            flex-direction: column; /* Ensure elements stack vertically */\n        }\n        #controls {\n            flex: 1 1 200px; /* Flex-grow, flex-shrink, flex-basis */\n            min-width: 180px;\n        }\n        #visualization {\n            flex: 2 1 400px; /* Take more space */\n            min-width: 400px; /* Ensure canvas has enough space */\n            align-items: center;\n        }\n        #output {\n            flex: 1 1 250px;\n            min-width: 220px;\n        }\n         #sequence-output {\n             flex: 1 1 100%; /* Take full width when wrapping */\n             margin-top: 15px; /* Add space when it wraps below */\n             max-height: 300px; /* Limit height and make scrollable */\n             overflow-y: auto;\n             border-top: 1px solid #ccc;\n             padding-top: 10px;\n         }\n        label {\n            display: block;\n            margin-top: 10px;\n            margin-bottom: 5px;\n            font-weight: bold;\n        }\n        input[type\u003d\"number\"] {\n            width: 90%;\n            padding: 8px;\n            margin-bottom: 10px;\n            border: 1px solid #ccc;\n            border-radius: 4px;\n        }\n        button {\n            padding: 10px 15px;\n            background-color: #007bff;\n            color: white;\n            border: none;\n            border-radius: 4px;\n            cursor: pointer;\n            font-size: 1em;\n            margin-top: 15px;\n            margin-right: 5px; /* Space between buttons */\n        }\n        button:hover {\n            background-color: #0056b3;\n        }\n         #share-button {\n             background-color: #28a745; /* Green for share */\n         }\n         #share-button:hover {\n             background-color: #218838;\n         }\n        #qaCanvas {\n            border: 1px solid #ccc;\n            background-color: #fdfdfd;\n            max-width: 100%;\n            height: auto;\n            aspect-ratio: 1 / 1; /* Keep canvas square */\n        }\n        #output h3, #sequence-output h3 {\n            margin-top: 0;\n            margin-bottom: 10px;\n        }\n        #output div, #sequence-output div {\n            margin-bottom: 10px;\n            padding: 8px;\n            background-color: #e9e9e9;\n            border-radius: 3px;\n            word-wrap: break-word;\n            font-size: 0.95em;\n        }\n         #output span, #sequence-output span {\n            font-weight: bold;\n            color: #333;\n         }\n         #harmonics-list {\n             list-style: none;\n             padding-left: 0;\n         }\n         #harmonics-list li {\n             display: inline-block;\n             margin-right: 5px;\n             margin-bottom: 3px;\n             background-color: lightcoral;\n             padding: 2px 5px;\n             border-radius: 3px;\n             font-size: 0.9em;\n         }\n        #equation-viewer {\n            margin-top: 15px;\n            padding: 10px;\n            background-color: #eef;\n            border: 1px dashed #aab;\n            border-radius: 4px;\n            font-family: monospace;\n            word-wrap: break-word;\n        }\n         .sequence-item {\n             border-bottom: 1px dotted #ccc;\n             margin-bottom: 8px;\n             padding-bottom: 8px;\n         }\n         .sequence-item:last-child {\n             border-bottom: none;\n         }\n\n    \u003c/style\u003e\n\u003c/head\u003e\n\u003cbody\u003e\n\n    \u003cdiv id\u003d\"controls\" class\u003d\"panel\"\u003e\n        \u003ch3\u003eControls\u003c/h3\u003e\n        \u003clabel for\u003d\"input-b\"\u003eInput b:\u003c/label\u003e\n        \u003cinput type\u003d\"number\" id\u003d\"input-b\" value\u003d\"3\"\u003e\n\n        \u003clabel for\u003d\"input-e\"\u003eInput e:\u003c/label\u003e\n        \u003cinput type\u003d\"number\" id\u003d\"input-e\" value\u003d\"4\"\u003e\n\n        \u003clabel for\u003d\"input-d\"\u003eInput d:\u003c/label\u003e\n        \u003cinput type\u003d\"number\" id\u003d\"input-d\" value\u003d\"5\"\u003e\n\n        \u003clabel for\u003d\"input-cycles\"\u003eNumber of Cycles:\u003c/label\u003e\n        \u003cinput type\u003d\"number\" id\u003d\"input-cycles\" value\u003d\"1\" min\u003d\"1\" max\u003d\"100\"\u003e \u003c!-- Added cycle input --\u003e\n\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n             \u003cbutton id\u003d\"run-op-button\"\u003eRun QA Operation(s)\u003c/button\u003e\n             \u003cbutton id\u003d\"share-button\"\u003eCopy Share URL\u003c/button\u003e \u003c!-- Added Share button --\u003e\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n        \u003cdiv id\u003d\"equation-viewer\"\u003e\n            \u003c!-- Symbolic equation will be displayed here --\u003e\n            a \u003d \u0026radic;[ b² + 2de + e² ]\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\n    \u003cdiv id\u003d\"visualization\" class\u003d\"panel\"\u003e\n        \u003ch3\u003eVisualization (Mod-24 Wheel)\u003c/h3\u003e\n        \u003ccanvas id\u003d\"qaCanvas\" width\u003d\"400\" height\u003d\"400\"\u003e\u003c/canvas\u003e\n        \u003cdiv id\u003d\"viz-info\" style\u003d\"margin-top: 10px; font-style: italic;\"\u003eMod-24 Wheel\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\n    \u003cdiv id\u003d\"output\" class\u003d\"panel\"\u003e\n        \u003ch3\u003eFinal State Output\u003c/h3\u003e\n         \u003c!-- Simplified: Shows only the *last* state --\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003eInitial QuNit:\u003cbr\u003e\n            b\u003d\u003cspan id\u003d\"initial-b\"\u003e?\u003c/span\u003e, e\u003d\u003cspan id\u003d\"initial-e\"\u003e?\u003c/span\u003e, d\u003d\u003cspan id\u003d\"initial-d\"\u003e?\u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003eFinal QuNit (After \u003cspan id\u003d\"cycle-count-final\"\u003e1\u003c/span\u003e cycle(s)):\u003cbr\u003e\n            b\u003d\u003cspan id\u003d\"output-b\"\u003e?\u003c/span\u003e, e\u003d\u003cspan id\u003d\"output-e\"\u003e?\u003c/span\u003e, d\u003d\u003cspan id\u003d\"output-d\"\u003e?\u003c/span\u003e, a\u003d\u003cspan id\u003d\"output-a\"\u003e?\u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003eMeasurement (Final State):\u003cbr\u003e\n            Rounded a: \u003cspan id\u003d\"measure-a\"\u003e?\u003c/span\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n            b/e Ratio: \u003cspan id\u003d\"measure-ratio\"\u003e?\u003c/span\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n            Is (b+e) Prime?: \u003cspan id\u003d\"measure-prime\"\u003e?\u003c/span\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n            Probabilistic Collapse: \u003cspan id\u003d\"measure-collapse\"\u003e?\u003c/span\u003e \u003c!-- Added Collapse field --\u003e\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n         \u003cdiv\u003eHarmonics (Aliquot Parts of Final \u0027a\u0027):\u003cbr\u003e\n             \u003cul id\u003d\"harmonics-list\"\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\n         \u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\n    \u003c!-- New panel for the sequence --\u003e\n    \u003cdiv id\u003d\"sequence-output\" class\u003d\"panel\"\u003e\n        \u003ch3\u003eOperation Sequence\u003c/h3\u003e\n        \u003c!-- Sequence details will be added here --\u003e\n        \u003cdiv id\u003d\"sequence-list\"\u003eRun simulation to see sequence...\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\n    \u003cscript\u003e\n        // --- DOM References ---\n        const inputB \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027input-b\u0027);\n        const inputE \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027input-e\u0027);\n        const inputD \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027input-d\u0027);\n        const inputCycles \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027input-cycles\u0027); // Cycle input\n        const runButton \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027run-op-button\u0027);\n        const shareButton \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027share-button\u0027); // Share button\n        const canvas \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027qaCanvas\u0027);\n        const ctx \u003d canvas.getContext(\u00272d\u0027);\n        const vizInfo \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027viz-info\u0027);\n        const equationViewer \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027equation-viewer\u0027);\n\n        const initialBOut \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027initial-b\u0027);\n        const initialEOut \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027initial-e\u0027);\n        const initialDOut \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027initial-d\u0027);\n        // Removed initialAOut as \u0027a\u0027 is derived within the transform\n\n        const cycleCountFinal \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027cycle-count-final\u0027);\n        const outputB \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027output-b\u0027);\n        const outputE \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027output-e\u0027);\n        const outputD \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027output-d\u0027);\n        const outputA \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027output-a\u0027);\n        const measureA \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027measure-a\u0027);\n        const measureRatio \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027measure-ratio\u0027);\n        const measurePrime \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027measure-prime\u0027);\n        const measureCollapse \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027measure-collapse\u0027); // Collapse output\n        const harmonicsList \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027harmonics-list\u0027);\n        const sequenceListDiv \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027sequence-list\u0027); // Sequence output div\n\n        // --- QA Simulation Functions ---\n\n        // Calculate \u0027a\u0027 based on b, e, d using the provided formula\n        function calculateA(b, e, d) {\n             // Handle potential non-numeric inputs gracefully\n             if (isNaN(b) || isNaN(e) || isNaN(d)) return NaN;\n             // Ensure non-negative result under the square root\n             const insideSqrt \u003d b*b + 2*d*e + e*e;\n             return (insideSqrt \u003e\u003d 0) ? Math.sqrt(insideSqrt) : NaN; // Return NaN if negative inside sqrt\n        }\n\n        function qaTransform(q_in) {\n            const b_in \u003d q_in.b;\n            const e_in \u003d q_in.e;\n            const d_in \u003d q_in.d;\n            const a_prev \u003d calculateA(b_in, e_in, d_in);\n\n            // Check for invalid previous \u0027a\u0027\n            if (isNaN(a_prev)) {\n                console.error(\"Invalid \u0027a\u0027 calculation in previous step. Cannot proceed.\");\n                return { b: NaN, e: NaN, d: NaN, a: NaN }; // Propagate error state\n            }\n\n            // Quanteus Transformation Logic (Example)\n            const b_out \u003d b_in + 1;\n            const e_out \u003d e_in + b_in;\n             // Use a_prev (a from input state) for d calculation. Ensure a_prev is non-negative.\n            const d_out \u003d (a_prev \u003e\u003d 0) ? Math.round(Math.sqrt(a_prev)) : 0;\n            const a_out \u003d calculateA(b_out, e_out, d_out);\n\n            return {\n                b: b_out,\n                e: e_out,\n                d: d_out,\n                a: a_out\n            };\n        }\n\n        // Probabilistic Collapse Function\n        function collapseToMeasurement(a) {\n            if (isNaN(a)) return NaN; // Handle invalid input\n            const floor \u003d Math.floor(a);\n            const ceil \u003d Math.ceil(a);\n            if (floor \u003d\u003d\u003d ceil) return floor; // If \u0027a\u0027 is already an integer\n\n            const probFloor \u003d ceil - a; // Probability of collapsing to floor\n            return Math.random() \u003c probFloor ? floor : ceil;\n        }\n\n        function measure(q) {\n             if (isNaN(q.a) || isNaN(q.b) || isNaN(q.e)) { // Check for invalid state\n                 return { rounded_a: \u0027N/A\u0027, ratio: \u0027N/A\u0027, primeRootCheck: \u0027N/A\u0027, collapsed_a: \u0027N/A\u0027 };\n             }\n            const ratio \u003d (q.e !\u003d\u003d 0) ? (q.b / q.e).toFixed(3) : \u0027Div/0\u0027;\n            const b_plus_e \u003d q.b + q.e; // Calculate once\n\n            return {\n                rounded_a: Math.round(q.a),\n                ratio: ratio,\n                // Check primality only if b+e is a valid number\n                primeRootCheck: !isNaN(b_plus_e) ? isPrime(Math.round(b_plus_e)) : false,\n                collapsed_a: collapseToMeasurement(q.a) // Add collapsed value\n            };\n        }\n\n        function getAliquotParts(n) {\n            if (isNaN(n) || n \u003c\u003d 0) return []; // Handle invalid or non-positive input\n            let num \u003d Math.round(n);\n            let parts \u003d [];\n            for (let i \u003d 1; i \u003c\u003d num / 2; i++) {\n                if (num % i \u003d\u003d\u003d 0) {\n                    parts.push(i);\n                }\n            }\n             // parts.push(num); // Optionally include the number itself\n            return parts;\n        }\n\n        function isPrime(num) {\n            if (isNaN(num)) return false; // Handle NaN input\n             num \u003d Math.floor(Math.abs(num)); // Work with positive integers\n            if (num \u003c\u003d 1) return false;\n            if (num \u003c\u003d 3) return true;\n            if (num % 2 \u003d\u003d\u003d 0 || num % 3 \u003d\u003d\u003d 0) return false;\n            for (let i \u003d 5; i * i \u003c\u003d num; i \u003d i + 6) {\n                if (num % i \u003d\u003d\u003d 0 || num % (i + 2) \u003d\u003d\u003d 0) return false;\n            }\n            return true;\n        }\n\n        // --- Visualization Function ---\n        function drawModWheel(modulus \u003d 24, highlightValue \u003d null) {\n            const radius \u003d Math.min(canvas.width, canvas.height) / 2 * 0.8;\n            const center \u003d { x: canvas.width / 2, y: canvas.height / 2 };\n            const pointRadius \u003d Math.min(15, Math.max(5, radius / modulus * 1.5)); // Adjust point size based on radius/modulus\n\n            ctx.clearRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);\n            ctx.beginPath();\n            ctx.arc(center.x, center.y, radius, 0, 2 * Math.PI);\n            ctx.strokeStyle \u003d \"#aaa\";\n            ctx.lineWidth \u003d 1;\n            ctx.stroke();\n\n            let highlightedIndex \u003d -1;\n             if (highlightValue !\u003d\u003d null \u0026\u0026 !isNaN(highlightValue)) {\n                 highlightedIndex \u003d Math.round(highlightValue) % modulus;\n                 if (highlightedIndex \u003c 0) highlightedIndex +\u003d modulus; // Handle negative modulo result\n             }\n\n            for (let i \u003d 0; i \u003c modulus; i++) {\n                let angle \u003d (2 * Math.PI * i / modulus) - (Math.PI / 2);\n                let x \u003d center.x + radius * Math.cos(angle);\n                let y \u003d center.y + radius * Math.sin(angle);\n\n                ctx.beginPath();\n                ctx.arc(x, y, pointRadius, 0, 2 * Math.PI);\n\n                if (i \u003d\u003d\u003d highlightedIndex) {\n                    ctx.fillStyle \u003d \"orange\";\n                    ctx.fill();\n                    ctx.strokeStyle \u003d \"black\";\n                    ctx.lineWidth \u003d 2;\n                } else {\n                     ctx.fillStyle \u003d i % 2 \u003d\u003d\u003d 0 ? \"lightblue\" : \"lightgreen\";\n                     ctx.fill();\n                     ctx.strokeStyle \u003d \"#555\";\n                     ctx.lineWidth \u003d 1;\n                }\n                 ctx.stroke();\n\n                ctx.fillStyle \u003d \"black\";\n                ctx.font \u003d `${Math.max(9, Math.min(12, pointRadius))}px sans-serif`; // Adjust font size\n                ctx.textAlign \u003d \"center\";\n                ctx.textBaseline \u003d \"middle\";\n                ctx.fillText(i, x, y);\n            }\n\n            if (highlightedIndex !\u003d\u003d -1) {\n                 vizInfo.textContent \u003d `Highlighting final ~a mod ${modulus} \u003d ${Math.round(highlightValue)} mod ${modulus} \u003d ${highlightedIndex}`;\n            } else if (highlightValue \u003d\u003d\u003d null) {\n                 vizInfo.textContent \u003d `Mod-${modulus} Wheel`;\n             } else { // Handle NaN case\n                  vizInfo.textContent \u003d `Mod-${modulus} Wheel (Invalid \u0027a\u0027 for highlighting)`;\n             }\n        }\n\n        // --- Update Display Functions ---\n        function updateFinalDisplay(initialQuNit, finalQuNit, measurement, harmonics, cycleCount) {\n            initialBOut.textContent \u003d initialQuNit.b;\n            initialEOut.textContent \u003d initialQuNit.e;\n            initialDOut.textContent \u003d initialQuNit.d;\n            cycleCountFinal.textContent \u003d cycleCount;\n\n            outputB.textContent \u003d isNaN(finalQuNit.b) ? \u0027Error\u0027 : finalQuNit.b;\n            outputE.textContent \u003d isNaN(finalQuNit.e) ? \u0027Error\u0027 : finalQuNit.e;\n            outputD.textContent \u003d isNaN(finalQuNit.d) ? \u0027Error\u0027 : finalQuNit.d;\n            outputA.textContent \u003d isNaN(finalQuNit.a) ? \u0027Error\u0027 : finalQuNit.a.toFixed(3);\n\n            measureA.textContent \u003d measurement.rounded_a;\n            measureRatio.textContent \u003d measurement.ratio;\n            measurePrime.textContent \u003d measurement.primeRootCheck ? \u0027Yes\u0027 : \u0027No\u0027;\n            measureCollapse.textContent \u003d measurement.collapsed_a;\n\n            harmonicsList.innerHTML \u003d \u0027\u0027;\n            if (harmonics.length \u003e 0) {\n                harmonics.forEach(part \u003d\u003e {\n                    const li \u003d document.createElement(\u0027li\u0027);\n                    li.textContent \u003d part;\n                    harmonicsList.appendChild(li);\n                });\n            } else {\n                 harmonicsList.innerHTML \u003d isNaN(finalQuNit.a) ? \u0027\u003cli\u003eError\u003c/li\u003e\u0027 : \u0027\u003cli\u003eNone\u003c/li\u003e\u0027;\n            }\n        }\n\n         function updateSequenceDisplay(sequence) {\n             sequenceListDiv.innerHTML \u003d \u0027\u0027; // Clear previous sequence\n             if (!sequence || sequence.length \u003d\u003d\u003d 0) {\n                 sequenceListDiv.textContent \u003d \u0027No sequence data generated.\u0027;\n                 return;\n             }\n\n             sequence.forEach((state,