3cdiv id\u003d\"controls\" class\u003d\"panel\"\u003e\n        \u003c!-- Forward Sim Controls (unchanged) --\u003e\n        \u003ch3\u003eForward Simulation Controls\u003c/h3\u003e\n        \u003clabel for\u003d\"input-b\"\u003eInitial b:\u003c/label\u003e \u003cinput type\u003d\"number\" id\u003d\"input-b\" value\u003d\"3\"\u003e\n        \u003clabel for\u003d\"input-e\"\u003eInitial e:\u003c/label\u003e \u003cinput type\u003d\"number\" id\u003d\"input-e\" value\u003d\"4\"\u003e\n        \u003clabel for\u003d\"input-d\"\u003eInitial d:\u003c/label\u003e \u003cinput type\u003d\"number\" id\u003d\"input-d\" value\u003d\"5\"\u003e\n        \u003clabel for\u003d\"input-cycles\"\u003eMax Cycles:\u003c/label\u003e \u003cinput type\u003d\"number\" id\u003d\"input-cycles\" value\u003d\"10\" min\u003d\"1\" max\u003d\"100\"\u003e\n        \u003cdiv class\u003d\"control-group\"\u003e\n             \u003cbutton id\u003d\"generate-button\"\u003eGenerate Sequence / Reset\u003c/button\u003e\n             \u003cbutton id\u003d\"share-button\"\u003eCopy Share URL\u003c/button\u003e\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \u003c!-- Animation Controls (unchanged) --\u003e\n        \u003cdiv class\u003d\"control-group\"\u003e\n            \u003clabel for\u003d\"speed-slider\"\u003eAnimation Speed (\u003cspan id\u003d\"speed-value\"\u003e500\u003c/span\u003ems):\u003c/label\u003e \u003cinput type\u003d\"range\" id\u003d\"speed-slider\" min\u003d\"50\" max\u003d\"2000\" value\u003d\"500\" step\u003d\"50\"\u003e\n            \u003cbutton id\u003d\"play-button\" disabled\u003ePlay ▶\u003c/button\u003e \u003cbutton id\u003d\"pause-button\" disabled\u003ePause ⏸\u003c/button\u003e \u003cbutton id\u003d\"reset-button\" disabled\u003eReset ⏮\u003c/button\u003e\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \u003cdiv id\u003d\"equation-viewer\"\u003eInitial state: a \u003d \u0026radic;[ b² + 2de + e² ]\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\n    \u003cdiv id\u003d\"reverse-controls\" class\u003d\"panel\"\u003e\n        \u003c!-- Reverse Controls (unchanged) --\u003e\n        \u003ch3\u003eReverse Operation\u003c/h3\u003e\n        \u003cp\u003eFind possible previous states (b, e, d) for a given (b\u0027, e\u0027, d\u0027).\u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003clabel for\u003d\"reverse-b\"\u003eInput b\u0027:\u003c/label\u003e \u003cinput type\u003d\"number\" id\u003d\"reverse-b\" value\u003d\"4\"\u003e\n        \u003clabel for\u003d\"reverse-e\"\u003eInput e\u0027:\u003c/label\u003e \u003cinput type\u003d\"number\" id\u003d\"reverse-e\" value\u003d\"7\"\u003e\n        \u003clabel for\u003d\"reverse-d\"\u003eInput d\u0027:\u003c/label\u003e \u003cinput type\u003d\"number\" id\u003d\"reverse-d\" value\u003d\"3\"\u003e\n        \u003cbutton id\u003d\"reverse-button\"\u003eFind Previous State(s)\u003c/button\u003e\n        \u003clabel style\u003d\"margin-top:15px;\"\u003ePossible Previous State(s):\u003c/label\u003e\n        \u003cdiv id\u003d\"reverse-output\"\u003eEnter values and click \"Find\".\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\n    \u003cdiv id\u003d\"visualization\" class\u003d\"panel\"\u003e\n        \u003ch3\u003eVisualization\u003c/h3\u003e\n        \u003cdiv style\u003d\"margin-bottom: 10px; text-align: center;\"\u003e\n             \u003clabel for\u003d\"show-resonances\"\u003eShow Resonant Intervals:\u003c/label\u003e\n             \u003cinput type\u003d\"checkbox\" id\u003d\"show-resonances\" checked\u003e\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \u003ccanvas id\u003d\"qaCanvas\" width\u003d\"400\" height\u003d\"400\"\u003e\u003c/canvas\u003e\n        \u003cdiv id\u003d\"viz-info\" style\u003d\"margin-top: 10px; font-style: italic;\"\u003eMod-24 Wheel\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\n    \u003cdiv id\u003d\"output\" class\u003d\"panel\"\u003e\n        \u003c!-- Output Panel (unchanged) --\u003e\n        \u003ch3 id\u003d\"output-title\"\u003eCurrent State Output (Step 0)\u003c/h3\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003eState at Step \u003cspan id\u003d\"current-step-display\"\u003e0\u003c/span\u003e:\u003c/div\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003eQuNit:\u003cbr\u003e b\u003d\u003cspan id\u003d\"output-b\"\u003e?\u003c/span\u003e, e\u003d\u003cspan id\u003d\"output-e\"\u003e?\u003c/span\u003e, d\u003d\u003cspan id\u003d\"output-d\"\u003e?\u003c/span\u003e, a\u003d\u003cspan id\u003d\"output-a\"\u003e?\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003eMeasurement:\u003cbr\u003e Rounded a: \u003cspan id\u003d\"measure-a\"\u003e?\u003c/span\u003e\u003cbr\u003e b/e Ratio: \u003cspan id\u003d\"measure-ratio\"\u003e?\u003c/span\u003e\u003cbr\u003e Is (b+e) Prime?: \u003cspan id\u003d\"measure-prime\"\u003e?\u003c/span\u003e\u003cbr\u003e Probabilistic Collapse: \u003cspan id\u003d\"measure-collapse\"\u003e?\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003eHarmonics (Aliquot Parts of \u0027a\u0027):\u003cbr\u003e \u003cul id\u003d\"harmonics-list\"\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\n    \u003cdiv id\u003d\"sequence-output\" class\u003d\"panel\"\u003e\n        \u003ch3\u003eQA Gate Sequence (\u003cspan id\u003d\"total-steps-display\"\u003e0\u003c/span\u003e steps)\u003c/h3\u003e\n         \u003c!-- Controls for sequence view --\u003e\n         \u003cdiv id\u003d\"sequence-controls\" style\u003d\"margin-bottom: 10px;\"\u003e\n             \u003clabel for\u003d\"highlight-primes\"\u003eHighlight Prime \u0027a\u0027 Steps:\u003c/label\u003e\n             \u003cinput type\u003d\"checkbox\" id\u003d\"highlight-primes\"\u003e\n         \u003c/div\u003e\n        \u003cdiv id\u003d\"sequence-list\"\u003eGenerate sequence to view steps...\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\n    \u003cscript\u003e\n        // --- DOM References --- (Added sequence controls)\n        /* ... existing DOM refs ... */\n        const highlightPrimesCheckbox \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027highlight-primes\u0027);\n        /* ... existing DOM refs ... */\n        const showResonancesCheckbox \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027show-resonances\u0027);\n        const reverseBInput \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027reverse-b\u0027); const reverseEInput \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027reverse-e\u0027); const reverseDInput \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027reverse-d\u0027); const reverseButton \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027reverse-button\u0027); const reverseOutputDiv \u003d document.getElementById(\u0027reverse-output\u0027);\n\n        // --- State Variables --- (Unchanged)\n        let fullSequence \u003d []; let currentStep \u003d 0; let isPlaying \u003d false;\n        let animationIntervalId \u003d null; let animationSpeedMs \u003d 500;\n\n        // --- Constants --- (Unchanged)\n        const resonanceRatios \u003d { /*...*/ }; const resonanceColors \u003d { /*...*/ }; const RESONANCE_TOLERANCE \u003d 0.1;\n\n        // --- QA Simulation Functions --- (Unchanged)\n        function calculateA(b, e, d) { /*...*/ } function qaTransform(q) { /*...*/ } function collapseToMeasurement(a) { /*...*/ } function measure(q) { /*...*/ } function getAliquotParts(n) { /*...*/ } function isPrime(num) { /*...*/ } function findPreviousState(b_next, e_next, d_next) { /*...*/ }\n\n        // --- Visualization Function --- (Unchanged)\n        function drawModWheel(modulus \u003d 24, highlightValue \u003d null, harmonics \u003d [], showResonances \u003d false) { /* ... (Unchanged from v2.4) ... */ }\n\n        // --- Update Display Functions --- (MODIFIED sequence display)\n        function updateStaticDisplays(initialState) {\n             updateEquationViewer(initialState.b, initialState.e, initialState.d);\n             displaySequenceList(fullSequence); // This now handles the gate view\n        }\n\n        function updateDynamicDisplays(stepIndex) {\n            if (stepIndex \u003c 0 || stepIndex \u003e\u003d fullSequence.length) { console.error(\"Invalid step index:\", stepIndex); pauseAnimation(); return; }\n            const state \u003d fullSequence[stepIndex];\n            const measurement \u003d measure(state);\n            const harmonics \u003d getAliquotParts(state.a);\n\n            // Update Output Panel (unchanged)\n            outputTitle.textContent \u003d `Current State Output (Step ${stepIndex})`; currentStepDisp.textContent \u003d stepIndex;\n            outputB.textContent \u003d isNaN(state.b)?\u0027Err\u0027:state.b; outputE.textContent \u003d isNaN(state.e)?\u0027Err\u0027:state.e; outputD.textContent \u003d isNaN(state.d)?\u0027Err\u0027:state.d; outputA.textContent \u003d isNaN(state.a)?\u0027Err\u0027:state.a.toFixed(3);\n            measureA.textContent \u003d measurement.rounded_a; measureRatio.textContent \u003d measurement.ratio; measurePrime.textContent \u003d measurement.primeRootCheck ? \u0027Yes\u0027 : \u0027No\u0027; measureCollapse.textContent \u003d measurement.collapsed_a;\n            harmonicsList.innerHTML \u003d \u0027\u0027; if (harmonics.length \u003e 0) { harmonics.forEach(part \u003d\u003e { const li\u003ddocument.createElement(\u0027li\u0027); li.textContent\u003dpart; harmonicsList.appendChild(li); }); } else { harmonicsList.innerHTML \u003d isNaN(state.a) ? \u0027\u003cli\u003eError\u003c/li\u003e\u0027 : \u0027\u003cli\u003eNone\u003c/li\u003e\u0027; }\n\n            // Update Visualization (unchanged call logic)\n            drawModWheel(24, state.a, harmonics, showResonancesCheckbox.checked);\n\n            // Highlight current step in the NEW sequence list view\n            highlightSequenceStep(stepIndex);\n        }\n\n        // MODIFIED function to display the gate sequence\n        function displaySequenceList(sequence) {\n             sequenceListDiv.innerHTML \u003d \u0027\u0027; // Clear previous list\n             totalStepsDisp.textContent \u003d sequence.length - 1;\n             if (!sequence || sequence.length \u003d\u003d\u003d 0) { sequenceListDiv.textContent \u003d \u0027No sequence generated.\u0027; return; }\n\n             const showPrimes \u003d highlightPrimesCheckbox.checked;\n\n             // Display initial state (Step 0)\n             const initialState \u003d sequence[0];\n             const step0Div \u003d createStepElement(initialState, 0, showPrimes);\n             sequenceListDiv.appendChild(step0Div);\n\n             // Display gates and subsequent states\n             for (let i \u003d 0; i \u003c sequence.length - 1; i++) {\n                 const currentState \u003d sequence[i];\n                 const nextState \u003d sequence[i+1];\n                 const gateIndex \u003d i + 1;\n\n                 // Create Gate Element\n                 const gateDiv \u003d document.createElement(\u0027div\u0027);\n                 gateDiv.classList.add(\u0027sequence-gate\u0027);\n                 gateDiv.id \u003d `gate-${gateIndex}`;\n                 gateDiv.innerHTML \u003d `\u003cdiv class\u003d\"gate-label\"\u003e⬇️ QA Gate ${gateIndex} ⬇️\u003c/div\u003e`;\n                 sequenceListDiv.appendChild(gateDiv);\n\n                 // Create Next Step Element\n                 const stepDiv \u003d createStepElement(nextState, gateIndex, showPrimes);\n                 sequenceListDiv.appendChild(stepDiv);\n             }\n             // Apply initial highlighting if needed\n             highlightSequenceStep(currentStep);\n         }\n\n         // Helper function to create a step element\n         function createStepElement(state, stepIndex, showPrimesHighlight) {\n             const stepDiv \u003d document.createElement(\u0027div\u0027);\n             stepDiv.classList.add(\u0027sequence-step\u0027);\n             stepDiv.id \u003d `step-${stepIndex}`;\n             const roundedA \u003d Math.round(state.a);\n             const isAPrime \u003d !isNaN(roundedA) \u0026\u0026 isPrime(roundedA);\n\n             stepDiv.innerHTML \u003d `\n                 \u003cstrong\u003eStep ${stepIndex}${stepIndex \u003d\u003d\u003d 0 ? \u0027 (Initial)\u0027 : \u0027\u0027}:\u003c/strong\u003e\n                 b\u003d\u003cspan\u003e${isNaN(state.b)?\u0027Err\u0027:state.b}\u003c/span\u003e,\n                 e\u003d\u003cspan\u003e${isNaN(state.e)?\u0027Err\u0027:state.e}\u003c/span\u003e,\n                 d\u003d\u003cspan\u003e${isNaN(state.d)?\u0027Err\u0027:state.d}\u003c/span\u003e,\n                 a\u003d\u003cspan\u003e${isNaN(state.a)?\u0027Err\u0027:state.a.toFixed(3)}\u003c/span\u003e\n                 ${isAPrime ? \u0027\u003cspan class\u003d\"prime-indicator\"\u003eA-PRIME\u003c/span\u003e\u0027 : \u0027\u0027}\n             `;\n\n             // Add highlighting class if prime highlighting is enabled and \u0027a\u0027 is prime\n             if (showPrimesHighlight \u0026\u0026 isAPrime) {\n                 stepDiv.classList.add(\u0027highlight-prime\u0027);\n             }\n\n             // Add click listener to jump to this step\n             stepDiv.addEventListener(\u0027click\u0027, () \u003d\u003e {\n                 pauseAnimation();\n                 currentStep \u003d stepIndex;\n                 updateDynamicDisplays(currentStep);\n                 updateAnimationButtons();\n             });\n             return stepDiv;\n         }\n\n\n        // MODIFIED to highlight both step and preceding gate (if applicable)\n        function highlightSequenceStep(stepIndex) {\n             // Remove highlight from all elements first\n             const activeItems \u003d sequenceListDiv.querySelectorAll(\u0027.active\u0027);\n             activeItems.forEach(item \u003d\u003e item.classList.remove(\u0027active\u0027));\n\n             // Add highlight to current step element\n             const currentStepItem \u003d document.getElementById(`step-${stepIndex}`);\n             if (currentStepItem) {\n                 currentStepItem.classList.add(\u0027active\u0027);\n                 // Scroll into view if needed\n                 currentStepItem.scrollIntoView({ behavior: \u0027smooth\u0027, block: \u0027nearest\u0027 });\n             }\n\n             // Also highlight the gate *leading* to this step (if not step 0)\n             if (stepIndex \u003e 0) {\n                  const precedingGateItem \u003d document.getElementById(`gate-${stepIndex}`);\n                  if (precedingGateItem) {\n                       precedingGateItem.classList.add(\u0027active\u0027); // Use same class or a different one? Let\u0027s try same.\n                  }\n             }\n         }\n\n        function updateEquationViewer(b, e, d) { /* ... (Unchanged) ... */ }\n        function updateAnimationButtons() { /* ... (Unchanged) ... */ }\n        function updateReverseOutput(result) { /* ... (Unchanged) ... */ }\n\n        // --- Animation Control Functions --- (Unchanged)\n        function playAnimation() { /*...*/ } function pauseAnimation() { /*...*/ } function resetSimulation() { /*...*/ }\n\n        // --- Event Listeners --- (Added prime highlight checkbox listener)\n        generateButton.addEventListener(\u0027click\u0027, () \u003d\u003e { /*...*/ pauseAnimation(); /*...*/ updateStaticDisplays(initialState); updateDynamicDisplays(currentStep); updateAnimationButtons(); });\n        playButton.addEventListener(\u0027click\u0027, playAnimation); pauseButton.addEventListener(\u0027click\u0027, pauseAnimation); resetButton.addEventListener(\u0027click\u0027, resetSimulation);\n        speedSlider.addEventListener(\u0027input\u0027, () \u003d\u003e { animationSpeedMs \u003d parseInt(speedSlider.value, 10); speedValueSpan.textContent \u003d animationSpeedMs; if (isPlaying) { pauseAnimation(); playAnimation(); } });\n        shareButton.addEventListener(\u0027click\u0027, () \u003d\u003e { /*...*/ });\n        reverseButton.addEventListener(\u0027click\u0027, () \u003d\u003e { /*...*/ });\n        showResonancesCheckbox.addEventListener(\u0027change\u0027, () \u003d\u003e { if (fullSequence.length \u003e 0) { updateDynamicDisplays(currentStep); } else { drawModWheel(24, null, [], showResonancesCheckbox.checked); } });\n\n        // Listener for the highlight primes checkbox\n         highlightPrimesCheckbox.addEventListener(\u0027change\u0027, () \u003d\u003e {\n             // Just re-render the sequence list to apply/remove highlighting classes\n             displaySequenceList(fullSequence);\n         });\n\n        // --- Initialization --- (Unchanged call order)\n        function initialize() { const urlParams \u003d new URLSearchParams(window.location.search); /*...*/ initializeUI(); generateButton.click(); }\n        function initializeUI() { /* Set up initial UI states */ speedValueSpan.textContent\u003dspeedSlider.value; animationSpeedMs\u003dparseInt(speedSlider.value,10); drawModWheel(24, null, [], showResonancesCheckbox.checked); }\n        initialize(); // Simplified call\n\n    \u003c/script\u003e\n\n\u003c/body\u003e\n\u003c/html\u003e\n```\n\n**Key Changes for QA Gate Explorer:**\n\n1.  **Sequence Panel Title:** Changed to \"QA Gate Sequence\".\n2.  **Sequence Controls:** Added a checkbox (`#highlight-primes`) to toggle highlighting of steps where the rounded `a` value is prime.\n3.  **CSS:** Added styles for `.sequence-step`, `.sequence-gate`, `.gate-label`, `.prime-indicator`, and the `.highlight-prime` class. Made steps clickable (`cursor: pointer`). Increased max-height of the panel.\n4.  **`displaySequenceList` Function (Major Change):**\n    *   Now iterates through the `fullSequence`.\n    *   For each step `i`, it creates:\n        *   A `div.sequence-step` for state `i`.\n        *   If `i \u003c sequence.length - 1`, it creates a `div.sequence-gate` representing the transition from step `i` to `i+1`.\n    *   Uses a helper `createStepElement` function to build the HTML for each step, including checking for primality and adding the `highlight-prime` class if the checkbox is checked and the condition met.\n5.  **`createStepElement` Helper:** Creates the HTML for a single step, adds the click listener for jumping, checks for prime \u0027a\u0027, and adds the relevant highlight class.\n6.  **`highlightSequenceStep` Function:** Now highlights both the active `div.sequence-step` *and* the `div.sequence-gate` that *leads into* that step (for steps \u003e 0).\n7.  **Event Listener (Highlight Primes):** Added a listener to the `#highlight-primes` checkbox. When changed, it simply calls `displaySequenceList` again to rebuild the list with the correct highlighting classes applied based on the new checkbox state.\n\n**How it Looks:**\n\n*   The \"Operation Sequence\" panel is now titled \"QA Gate Sequence\".\n*   You see a vertical flow: State 0 -\u003e Gate 1 -\u003e State 1 -\u003e Gate 2 -\u003e State 2...\n*   Each state (`.sequence-step`) shows its b, e, d, a values and is clickable to jump the simulation.\n*   Between states, a simple label (`.sequence-gate`) indicates the transformation step.\n*   Checking \"Highlight Prime \u0027a\u0027 Steps\" will add a distinct border/shadow to steps where the rounded `a` value is prime.\n*   The animation correctly highlights the active step and the gate leading to it.\n\nThis provides a much clearer view of the simulation as a computational process unfolding through discrete gate applications.\n\nWhat\u0027s the next frontier? **Export Mode (3)** for practical utility seems like a strong candidate!",
